response.Q0: I decided on a more systematic approach where I would inspect all the edge nodes that were at the bottom left, then the ones at the top and finally the ones at the bottom right.
response.Q1: Yes. At first it was to find the path that would yield the most, but that approach was costly, especially considering that the only nodes that paid the most were the ones at the edges. I decided on using the node inspector on the nodes that were at the edges, I did it haphazardly at first and it felt too costly also, so I decided on a more systematic approach where I would inspect all the edge nodes that were at the bottom left, then the ones at the top and finally the ones at the bottom right.
response.Q2: I found it quite difficult. The most difficult part was to reduce the cost of the node inspection, while at the same time increasing the amount I was accumulating.
